<title>GHANA: Two trains collide in Ghana, 59 wounded.</title>
<headline>Two trains collide in Ghana, 59 wounded.</headline>
<dateline>ACCRA 1997-02-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Two passenger trains collided in southern central Ghana injuring 59 people, state radio reported on Saturdau.</p>
<p>Friday's accident, at Bekwai, 30 km south of Kumasi, occured after one train failed to stop at a station, the radio said.</p>
<p>Three of the injured were admitted to hospital, the rest discharged after treatment.</p>
